<paragraph id="795CAA05DD0B020C82F082503C2C22DA" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ED90D2319268F447C010C0AC2EAE5449" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="143" pageId="13" pageNumber="142">
<taxonomicName id="782CA0602B25F72F9C4DF20983A4E435" class="Reptilia" family="Elapidae" genus="Hydrophis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hydrophis platurus" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platurus">Hydrophis platurus</taxonomicName>
is distinguishable from other species in the region by having a unique color pattern (see above). 
<taxonomicName id="8EC7105B3D7CD8EDA4AE86D15D409428" class="Reptilia" family="Elapidae" genus="Hydrophis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hydrophis platurus" order="Squamata" pageId="13" pageNumber="142" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="platurus">Hydrophis platurus</taxonomicName>
has been known as the only planktonic tetrapod, spending a considerable portion of its life floating at the depth of 20-50 m, but preying on fish at the sea surface by float-and-wait feeding strategy, passively drifting with surface and subsurface marine currents. It has consequently the widest distribution of all squamatan reptiles (
<bibRefCitation id="B6ED7456054D8BF029F83DB108AA7FFE" author="Cook, TR" journalOrPublisher="Animal Behaviour" pageId="26" pageNumber="155" pagination="113 - 123" title="Why does the only ' planktonic tetrapod' dive? Determinates of diving behaviour in a marine ectotherm." url="10.1016/j.anbehav.2014.09.018" volume="98" year="2014">Cook and Brischoux 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="185329AC642242A6E7852E8EB55557EC" author="Hecht, MK" journalOrPublisher="Herpetologica" pageId="27" pageNumber="156" pagination="387 - 396" title="Distribution of the yellow-bellied sea snake, Pelamisplaturus, and its significance in relation to the fossil record." volume="30" year="1974">Hecht et al. 1974</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="DDBD5232B1772227743F223841C66217" author="Sheehy, III CM" journalOrPublisher="Integrative and Comparative Biology" pageId="29" pageNumber="158" pagination="321 - 330" title="Preliminary insights into the phylogeography of the yellow-bellied sea snake, Pelamisplaturus." url="10.1093/icb/ics088" volume="52" year="2012">Sheehy III et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
). None of the specimens collected in this project were 
<pageBreakToken id="60B73A345C03531B6D0D8A0B4E35CE66" pageId="14" pageNumber="143" start="start">from</pageBreakToken>
the Persian Gulf, although there are records from the Persian Gulf (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="CE9769DB222FAF332EBD0C2B128D2942" author="Eissa, SM" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Kuwait University" pageId="26" pageNumber="155" pagination="123 - 146" title="Record of certain reptilian species found in Kuwait." volume="2" year="1975">Eissa and El-Assy 1975</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="006D8A3BC826E2270EFC99AD3C2A6544" author="Gallagher, MD" journalOrPublisher="Published by the author, Bahrain" pageId="26" pageNumber="155" title="The amphibians and reptiles of Bahrain." year="1971">Gallagher 1971</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="6C44F5E1A870F95A0525AABDE49CF620" author="Soorae, PS" journalOrPublisher="Zoology in the Middle East" pageId="29" pageNumber="158" pagination="109 - 110" title="Records of sea snakes (subfamily Hydrophiinae) from the coastal waters of the Abu Dhabi Emirate, United Arab Emirates." url="10.1080/09397140.2006.10638191" volume="39" year="2006">Soorae et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="2CBAB9C7EC2B77425FE105AF0E8BB1BC" author="Volsoe, H" editor="Jessen, K" journalOrPublisher="Copenhagen" pageId="30" pageNumber="159" pagination="9 - 45" title="The sea snakes of the Iranian Gulf and the Gulf of Oman, with a summary of the biology of the sea snakes." volumeTitle="Danish Scientific Investigations in Iran" year="1939">
<normalizedToken id="67906F0887049AE34BDED2EB367D213E" originalValue="Volsøe">Volsoe</normalizedToken>
1939
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5BEB0BC877CE3F776499B60A55A26C82" author="Werner, F" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="30" pageNumber="159" pagination="13 - 20" title="Ueber eine sammlung von Reptilien aus Persien, Mesopotamien und Arabien." url="10.5962/bhl.part.26910" volume="45" year="1895">Werner 1895</bibRefCitation>
).
